lower than expected from a standard NFW halo\n($\\sigma_{\\rm halo}\\sim 30$ km/s). We conclude that NGC1052-DF2 is not an\nisolated case but that a class of such objects exists. The origin of these\nlarge, faint galaxies with an excess of luminous globular clusters and an\napparent lack of dark matter is, at present, not understood.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Jan 2019 19:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Mar 2019 11:38:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 15 Mar 2019 11:12:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-03"}
